From: DNN-Opt Developer <dnnopt@example.com>
Date: Sat, 25 Apr 2026 02:44:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] feat: Integrate DNN-Opt into brgemm_matmul for
 small/irregular shapes

Add hybrid dispatch in brgemm_matmul_t::execute_body() to use DNN-Opt's
optimized GEMM kernels for small and irregular matrix shapes while
keeping brgemm kernel for large regular shapes.

Changes:
- brgemm_matmul_utils.hpp: Add should_use_dnnopt_shape() function and
  use_dnnopt flag in brgemm_matmul_conf_t
- brgemm_matmul.hpp: Add should_use_dnnopt() and execute_dnnopt() methods
- brgemm_matmul.cpp: Implement DNN-Opt dispatch in execute_body()
- cmake/dnnopt.cmake: Fix library linking configuration

Shape detection rules for DNN-Opt:
- M <= 16: tiny/small_m kernels
- M <= 32 && N <= 128 && K <= 128: small square-ish
- M*N*K < 32768: very small total ops
- M <= 64 && !is_pow2(M): irregular M dimensions

This enables DNN-Opt optimization on SVE_512/SVE_256 capable servers
where brgemm_matmul would normally be selected.

