+# DNN-Opt Integration into brgemm_matmul for oneDNN v3.7
+
+## Overview
+
+This document describes how to integrate DNN-Opt's optimized GEMM for small/irregular shapes
+into oneDNN v3.7's `brgemm_matmul_t` primitive on AArch64.
+
+## Problem Statement
+
+- `brgemm_matmul_t` is selected for matmul on SVE_512/SVE_256 capable hardware
+- brgemm_matmul uses JIT-compiled SVE kernels that are optimized for large matrices
+- DNN-Opt provides optimized GEMM for small matrices (M <= 16) and irregular shapes
+- Current DNN-Opt patches in `gemm.cpp` (`extended_sgemm`) are bypassed when brgemm is used
+
+## Integration Strategy
+
+### Approach: Hybrid Dispatch in brgemm_matmul
+
+Modify `brgemm_matmul_t::execute_body()` to:
+1. Check if the shape falls into DNN-Opt's optimization domain
+2. If yes, call DNN-Opt's `gemm_fp32()` directly
+3. If no, proceed with original brgemm kernel execution
+
+### Shape Classification
+
+DNN-Opt excels at:
+- Small M: M <= 16 (tiny/small_m_wide kernels)
+- Irregular shapes: prime dimensions, non-power-of-2
+- Very small batch: M <= 4, N <= 16
+
+```cpp
+inline bool should_use_dnnopt(int M, int N, int K) {
+    // DNN-Opt optimized shapes
+    if (M <= 16 && N >= 1 && K >= 1) return true;
+    if (M <= 32 && N <= 64 && K <= 64) return true;  // small square-ish
+    if (M * N * K < 16384) return true;  // very small total ops
+    
+    // Irregular shapes
+    if (!is_pow2(M) && M <= 64) return true;
+    
+    return false;
+}
+```
+
+## Implementation Details
+
+### File 1: src/cpu/aarch64/matmul/brgemm_matmul.hpp
+
+Add DNN-Opt header include and helper function:
+
+```cpp
+// At the top of the file, after existing includes
+#ifdef DNNL_USE_DNNOPT
+#include "dnnopt/gemm/gemm.h"
+#endif
+
+// In the brgemm_matmul_t class, add private method
+private:
+    bool should_use_dnnopt() const;
+    status_t execute_dnnopt(const exec_ctx_t &ctx) const;
+```
+
+### File 2: src/cpu/aarch64/matmul/brgemm_matmul.cpp
+
+#### 2a. Add shape detection in pd_t::init
+
+```cpp
+// In pd_t::init(), after all validation checks pass
+template <cpu_isa_t isa>
+status_t brgemm_matmul_t<isa>::pd_t::init(engine_t *engine) {
+    // ... existing validation code ...
+    
+    // Set flag for DNN-Opt usage
+    bgmmc_.use_dnnopt = should_use_dnnopt_shape(bgmmc_.M, bgmmc_.N, bgmmc_.K);
+    
+    // ... rest of init ...
+}
+
+inline bool should_use_dnnopt_shape(dim_t M, dim_t N, dim_t K) {
+    if (M <= 0 || N <= 0 || K <= 0) return false;
+    
+    // DNN-Opt sweet spots
+    if (M <= 16) return true;  // tiny/small_m
+    if (M <= 32 && N <= 128) return true;  // small_m_wide
+    if (M * N * K < 32768) return true;  // very small total
+    
+    // Irregular: prime or non-power-of-2 small M
+    if (M <= 64 && !is_pow2(M)) return true;
+    
+    return false;
+}
+```
+
+#### 2b. Add execute_dnnopt method
+
+```cpp
+template <cpu_isa_t isa>
+bool brgemm_matmul_t<isa>::should_use_dnnopt() const {
+    const auto &bgmmc = pd()->get_brgemm_matmul_conf();
+    return bgmmc.use_dnnopt;
+}
+
+template <cpu_isa_t isa>
+status_t brgemm_matmul_t<isa>::execute_dnnopt(const exec_ctx_t &ctx) const {
+    const auto src_d = ctx.memory_mdw(DNNL_ARG_SRC, pd()->src_md());
+    const auto weights_d = ctx.memory_mdw(DNNL_ARG_WEIGHTS, pd()->weights_md());
+    const auto dst_d = ctx.memory_mdw(DNNL_ARG_DST, pd()->dst_md());
+    
+    const float *src = static_cast<const float *>(
+            CTX_IN_MEM(const char *, DNNL_ARG_SRC));
+    const float *weights = static_cast<const float *>(
+            CTX_IN_MEM(const char *, DNNL_ARG_WEIGHTS));
+    float *dst = static_cast<float *>(
+            CTX_OUT_MEM(char *, DNNL_ARG_DST));
+    
+    const auto &bgmmc = pd()->get_brgemm_matmul_conf();
+    const dim_t M = bgmmc.M;
+    const dim_t N = bgmmc.N;
+    const dim_t K = bgmmc.K;
+    
+    // Get strides from memory descriptors
+    const dim_t lda = src_d.blocking_desc().strides[bgmmc.ndims - 1];
+    const dim_t ldb = weights_d.blocking_desc().strides[bgmmc.ndims - 2];
+    const dim_t ldc = dst_d.blocking_desc().strides[bgmmc.ndims - 1];
+    
+    // Handle batch dimension
+    const dim_t batch = bgmmc.batch;
+    
+    for (dim_t b = 0; b < batch; b++) {
+        const float *A_batch = src + b * bgmmc.A_strides[2] / sizeof(float);
+        const float *B_batch = weights + b * bgmmc.B_strides[2] / sizeof(float);
+        float *C_batch = dst + b * bgmmc.C_strides[2] / sizeof(float);
+        
+        // Call DNN-Opt GEMM
+        dnnopt::gemm_fp32(M, N, K, 1.0f, A_batch, lda,
+                         B_batch, ldb, 0.0f, C_batch, ldc);
+    }
+    
+    return status::success;
+}
+```
+
+#### 2c. Modify execute_body to dispatch
+
+```cpp
+template <cpu_isa_t isa>
+status_t brgemm_matmul_t<isa>::execute_body(const exec_ctx_t &ctx) const {
+    // Check if DNN-Opt should be used
+#ifdef DNNL_USE_DNNOPT
+    if (should_use_dnnopt()) {
+        return execute_dnnopt(ctx);
+    }
+#endif
+    
+    // ... existing brgemm execution code ...
+}
+```
+
