+### File 4: cmake/dnnopt.cmake (same as before)
+
+```cmake
+# DNN-Opt finder for oneDNN v3.7
+find_path(DNNOPT_INCLUDE_DIR
+    NAMES dnnopt/gemm/gemm.h
+    PATHS ${DNNOPT_ROOT}/include
+)
+
+find_library(DNNOPT_LIBRARY
+    NAMES dnnopt_core
+    PATHS ${DNNOPT_ROOT}/build ${DNNOPT_ROOT}/lib
+)
+
+if(DNNOPT_INCLUDE_DIR AND DNNOPT_LIBRARY)
+    message(STATUS "Found DNN-Opt: ${DNNOPT_LIBRARY}")
+    add_definitions(-DDNNL_USE_DNNOPT)
+    
+    # Add DNN-Opt as link dependency
+    set(DNNL_LINK_LIBS "${DNNL_LINK_LIBS};${DNNOPT_LIBRARY}" PARENT_SCOPE)
+    include_directories(${DNNOPT_INCLUDE_DIR})
+else()
+    message(STATUS "DNN-Opt not found, using oneDNN native kernels")
+endif()
+```
+
+## Testing Strategy
+
+### Test Script
+
+```bash
+#!/bin/bash
+# Test DNN-Opt integration in brgemm_matmul
+
+SHAPES=(
+    "16x32:32x16"   # small_m - should use DNN-Opt
+    "4x32:32x16"    # tiny - should use DNN-Opt  
+    "35x400:400x400" # irregular M - should use DNN-Opt
+    "256x256:256x256" # large - should use brgemm
+)
+
+for shape in "${SHAPES[@]}"; do
+    echo "Testing $shape"
+    DNNL_VERBOSE=1 LD_LIBRARY_PATH=./src ./tests/benchdnn/benchdnn \
+        --matmul --mode=P --dt=f32 $shape 2>&1 | grep "matmul,"
+    
+    # Verify:
+    # - Small shapes show kernel name containing "dnnopt" or similar marker
+    # - Large shapes show "brg:sve_512" or "brg:sve_256"
+done
+```
+
+## Expected Performance
+
+| Shape | oneDNN brgemm (GF) | DNN-Opt (GF) | Expected Improvement |
+|-------|-------------------|---------------|---------------------|
+| 16x32:32x16 | ~6.7 | ~11.2 | +67% |
+| 4x32:32x16 | ~2.1 | ~5.6 | +167% |
+| 35x400:400x400 | ~15.4 | ~36.6 | +137% |
+| 256x256:256x256 | ~43.7 | ~43 | Similar (brgemm) |
+
+## Alternative Approach: Fallback at Primitive Selection
+
+Instead of modifying brgemm_matmul, we could modify the primitive selection logic:
+
+### cpu_matmul_list.cpp modification
+
+```cpp
+// Add a new primitive for DNN-Opt matmul before brgemm
+#ifdef DNNL_USE_DNNOPT
+CPU_INSTANCE_AARCH64(dnnopt_matmul_t)  // New primitive for small shapes
+#endif
+
+CPU_INSTANCE_AARCH64(brgemm_matmul_t<sve_512>)
+// ... rest ...
+```
+
+This requires creating a new `dnnopt_matmul_t` primitive class that wraps DNN-Opt's gemm_fp32.
+
+## Recommended Implementation Order
+
+1. **Phase 1**: Modify brgemm_matmul with hybrid dispatch (simpler, less invasive)
+2. **Phase 2**: If needed, create dedicated dnnopt_matmul_t primitive for better separation
+3. **Phase 3**: Add autotune support for shape-based kernel selection
